    "scenario": "SCENARIO(46-47)\nJavier is a member of the fitness club EVERFIT. This company has branches in many EU member states, but for the purposes of the GDPR maintains its primary establishment in France. Javier lives in Newry, Northern Ireland (part of the U.K.), and commutes across the border to work in Dundalk, Ireland. Two years ago while on a business trip, Javier was photographed while working out at a branch of EVERFIT in Frankfurt, Germany. At the time, Javier gave his consent to being included in the photograph, since he was told that it would be used for promotional purposes only. Since then, the photograph has been used in the club's U.K. brochures, and it features in the landing page of its U.K. website. However, the  fitness club has recently fallen into disrepute due to widespread  mistreatment of members at various branches of the club in several EU member states. As a result, Javier no longer feels comfortable with his photograph being publicly associated with the fitness club.(涉及被遗忘权)\n场景题（46-47题）\n哈维尔（Javier）是健身俱乐部 EVERFIT 的会员。该公司在多个欧盟成员国设有分支机构，但就GDPR而言，其主要营业地位于法国。哈维尔居住在北爱尔兰纽里（属于英国），每日跨境通勤至爱尔兰邓多克工作。两年前，哈维尔在德国法兰克福的 EVERFIT 分支机构健身时被拍照。当时，他被告知该照片仅用于促销目的，因此同意被纳入照片中。自那以后，该照片被用于该俱乐部的英国宣传册，并出现在其英国网站的着陆页上。然而，由于该健身俱乐部在多个欧盟成员国的多家分支机构普遍存在虐待会员的情况，其声誉近期一落千丈。因此，哈维尔不再愿意自己的照片与该健身俱乐部公开关联。\nAfter numerous failed attempts to book an appointment with the manager of the local branch to discuss this matter, Javier sends a letter to EVETFIT requesting that his image be removed from the website and all promotional materials. Months pass and Javier, having received no acknowledgment of his request, becomes very anxious about this matter. After repeatedly failing to contact EVETFIT through alternate channels, he decides to take action against the company.\nJavier contacts the U.K. Information Commissioner's Office (ICO - the U.K.'s supervisory authority) to lodge a complaint about this matter. The ICO, pursuant to Article 56(3) of the GDPR, informs the CNIL (i.e. the supervisory authority of EVERFIT's main establishment) about this matter. Despite the fact that EVERFIT has an establishment in the U.K., the CNIL decides to handle the case in accordance with Article 60 of the GDPR. The CNIL liaises with the ICO, as relevant under the cooperation procedure. In light of issues amongst the supervisory authorities to reach a decision, the European Data Protection Board becomes involved and, pursuant to the consistency mechanism, issues a binding decision.\nAdditionally, Javier sues EVERFIT for the damages caused as a result of its failure to honor his request to have his photograph removed from the brochure and website.\n哈维尔多次尝试预约当地分支机构经理讨论此事，但均未成功，随后他向 EVERFIT 发送信函，要求将其影像从网站及所有宣传材料中删除。数月过去，哈维尔未收到任何关于其请求的回复，对此事感到非常焦虑。在通过其他渠道多次联系 EVERFIT 未果后，他决定对该公司采取法律行动。\n哈维尔联系英国信息专员办公室（ICO，英国的监管机构）就此事项提出投诉。根据GDPR第56条第3款，英国信息专员办公室将此事通知了法国国家信息与自由委员会（CNIL，即 EVERFIT 主要营业地的监管机构）。尽管 EVERFIT 在英国设有分支机构，但法国国家信息与自由委员会（CNIL）决定根据GDPR第60条处理此案。法国国家信息与自由委员会（CNIL）按照合作程序的相关规定，与英国信息专员办公室（ICO）进行了联络。由于各监管机构在达成决定方面存在分歧，欧洲数据保护委员会介入，并根据一致性机制发布了具有约束力的决定。\n此外，哈维尔就EVERFIT未履行其删除宣传册和网站中其照片的请求所造成的损害对该公司提起诉讼。"
