    "answer": "A",
    "correct": "A",
    "explanation": "根据GDPR的规定，收集特殊类别的个人数据，例如地点信息，需要得到用户的明确同意。这不仅涉及到获取同意，还包括在用户选择撤销同意时尊重用户的选择。因此Who-R-U必须在开始追踪之前，清楚地告知用户其数据收集的目的，以及用户的权利，并得到他们的明确同意。根据GDPR的规定，收集特殊类别的个人数据，例如地点信息，需要得到用户的明确同意。这不仅涉及到获取同意，还包括在用户选择撤销同意时尊重用户的选择。因  此Who-R-U必须在开始追踪之前，清楚地告知用户其数据收集的目的以及用户的权利，并得到他们的明确同意。\nTracking locations - special categories - consent\nlocation information是特殊类别数据：虽然第九条special category没有列举到location information，但根据EDPB对于特殊数据的解释来看：特殊数据应按照推理而非单纯的列举，location information可以推理为特殊数据：通过观察某个人长期去教堂可以看出宗教信仰、经常去LGBT可以看出性取向、经常去医院可以看出健康状况。",
    "groupId": "scenario-83-86",
    "scenarioTitle": "材料题 83-86",
    "scenario": "SCENARIO(83-86)\nJoe is the new privacy manager for Who-R-U, a Canadian business that provides DNA analysis. The company is headquartered in Montreal, and all of its employees are located there. The company offers its services to Canadians only:Its website is in English and French, it accepts only Canadian currency, and it blocks internet traffic from outside of Canada (although this solution doesn't prevent all non-Canadian traffic). It also declines to process orders that request the DNA report to be sent outside of Canada, and returns orders that show a non-Canadian return address.\nBob, the President of Who-R-U, thinks there is a lot of interest for the product in the EU, and the company is exploring a number of plans to expand its customer base.\n场景题（83-86 题）\n乔（Joe）是 Who-R-U 公司的新任隐私经理，该公司是一家提供 DNA 分析服务的加拿大企业，总部位于蒙特利尔，所有员工均在此办公。公司仅向加拿大人提供服务：其网站采用英语和法语，仅接受加拿大货币支付，并屏蔽来自加拿大境外的互联网流量（尽管该解决方案无法阻止所有非加拿大流量）。公司还拒绝处理要求将 DNA 报告发送至加拿大境外的订单，并会退回显示非加拿大退货地址的订单。\nWho-R-U 公司总裁鲍勃（Bob）认为欧盟市场对该产品存在大量需求，公司正探索多项计划以扩大客户群。\nThe first plan, collegially called We-Track-U, will use an app to collect information about its current Canadian customer base. The expansion will allow its Canadian customers to use the app while traveling abroad. He suggests that the company use this app to gather location information. If the plan shows promise, Bob proposes to use push notifications and text messages to encourage existing customers to pre-register for an EU version of the service. Bob calls this work plan, We-Text-U. Once the company has gathered enough pre-registrations, it will develop EU-specific content and services.\nAnother plan is called Customer for Life. The idea is to offer additional services through the company's app, like storage and sharing of DNA information with other applications and medical providers. The company's contract says that it can keep customer DNA indefinitely, and use it to offer new services and market them to customers. It also says that customers agree not to withdraw direct marketing consent. Paul, the marketing director, suggests that the company should fully exploit these provisions, and that it can work around customers' attempts to withdraw consent because the contract invalidates them.\n第一项计划名为 “We-Track-U”（我们追踪你），将通过一款应用程序收集其现有加拿大客户群的信息。此次扩展将允许其加拿大客户在海外旅行时使用该应用程序。他建议公司利用该应用程序收集位置信息。如果该计划成效良好，鲍勃提议通过推送通知和短信鼓励现有客户预先注册该服务的欧盟版本，他将此工作计划称为 “We-Text-U”（我们给你发短信）。一旦公司收集到足够的预注册量，将开发针对欧盟市场的专属内容和服务。\n另一项计划名为 “终身客户”（Customer for Life）。其核心是通过公司应用程序提供额外服务，例如 DNA 信息的存储以及与其他应用程序和医疗服务提供者共享该信息。公司合同规定，可无限期保留客户的 DNA 数据，并利用该数据提供新服务且向客户推广。合同还规定，客户同意不撤回对直接营销的同意。营销总监保罗（Paul）建议公司应充分利用这些条款，且由于合同已使客户撤回同意的行为无效，因此可以规避客户的撤回尝试。\nThe final plan is to develop a brand presence in the EU. The company has already begun this process. It is in the process of purchasing the naming rights for a building in Germany, which would come with a few offices that Who-R-U executives can use while traveling internationally. The office doesn't include any technology or infrastructure; rather, it's simply a room with a desk and some chairs.\nOn a recent trip concerning the naming-rights deal, Bob's laptop is stolen. The laptop held unencrypted DNA reports on 5,000 Who-R-U customers, all of whom are residents of Canada. The reports include customer name, birth date, ethnicity ,racial background, names of relatives, gender, and occasionally health information.\n最后一项计划是在欧盟建立品牌影响力。公司已启动相关流程，正在洽谈购买德国一栋建筑的命名权，该建筑将附带几间办公室，供 Who-R-U 公司高管在国际旅行时使用。这些办公室不配备任何技术设备或基础设施，仅为一间带有办公桌和椅子的房间。\n在最近一次与命名权交易相关的旅行中，鲍勃的笔记本电脑被盗。该电脑存储了5000名Who-R-U公司客户的未加密 DNA 报告，所有客户均为加拿大居民。报告包含客户姓名、出生日期、民族、种族背景、亲属姓名、性别，有时还包括健康信息。"
