    "scenarioTitle": "材料题 125-129",
    "scenario": "SCENARIO(125-129)\nJane starts her new role as a Data Protection Officer (DPO) at a Malta-based company that allows anyone to buy and sell cryptocurrencies via its online platform. The company stores and processes the personal data of its customers in a dedicated data center located in Malta (EU).\nPeople wishing to trade cryptocurrencies are required to open an online account on the platform. They then must successfully pass a Know Your Customer (KYC) due diligence procedure aimed at preventing money laundering and ensuring compliance with applicable financial regulations.\nThe non-European customers are also required to waive all their GDPR rights by reading a disclaimer written in bold and ticking a checkbox on a separate page to get their account approved on the platform.\n场景题（125-129题）\n简（Jane）新任马耳他某公司的数据保护官（DPO），该公司通过其在线平台为任何人提供加密货币买卖服务。公司在马耳他（欧盟国家）的专用数据中心存储和处理客户的个人数据。\n希望交易加密货币的个人需在平台上开设在线账户，然后必须成功通过 “了解你的客户”（KYC）尽职调查程序，该程序旨在防止洗钱并确保遵守适用的金融法规。非欧洲客户还需阅读加粗显示的免责声明并在单独页面勾选方框，放弃其所有GDPR项下的权利，才能获得平台账户批准。\nAll customers must likewise accept the terms of service of the platform. The terms of service also include a privacy policy section, saying, among other things, that if a customer fails the KYC process, its KYC data will be automatically shared with the national anti-money laundering agency. The KYC procedure requires customers to answer many questions, including whether they have any criminal convictions, whether they use recreational drugs or have problems with alcohol, and whether they have a terminal illness. While providing this data, customers see a conspicuous message saying that this data is meant only to prevent fraud and account takeover and will be never shared with private third parties.\n所有客户均需接受平台的服务条款。服务条款中包含隐私政策部分，其中规定，若客户未通过 KYC 程序，其 KYC 数据将自动共享给国家反洗钱机构。KYC 程序要求客户回答多个问题，包括是否有犯罪记录、是否使用娱乐性药物或有酗酒问题，以及是否患有绝症。客户提供这些数据时，会看到一条醒目的提示，说明这些数据仅用于防止欺诈和账户被盗，绝不会与私人第三方共享。\nThe company regularly conducts external security testing of its online systems by independent cybersecurity companies from the EU. At the final stage of testing, the company provides cybersecurity assessors with access to its central database to review security permissions, roles and policies. Personal data in the database is encrypted; however, cybersecurity assessors usually have access to the decryption keys obtained while running initial security testing. The assessors must strictly follow the guidelines imposed by the company during the entire testing and auditing process. All customer data, including trading activities and all internal communications with technical support, are permanently stored in a secured AWS S3 Glacier cloud data storage, located in Ireland, for backup and compliance purposes. The data is securely transferred to the cloud and then is properly encrypted while at rest by using AWS-native encryption mechanisms. These mechanisms give AWS the necessary technical means to encrypt and decrypt the data when such is required by the company. There is no data processing agreement between AWS and the company.\n公司定期聘请欧盟的独立网络安全公司对其在线系统进行外部安全测试。在测试的最后阶段，公司向网络安全评估人员提供中央数据库的访问权限，以便其审查安全权限、角色和政策。数据库中的个人数据已加密，但网络安全评估人员通常能在初始安全测试过程中获取解密密钥。评估人员在整个测试和审计过程中必须严格遵守公司制定的指南。所有客户数据（包括交易活动和与技术支持的所有内部沟通）均永久存储在爱尔兰的AWS S3 Glacier云存储中，用于备份和合规目的。数据通过安全方式传输至云端，并在静态存储时使用AWS原生加密机制进行适当加密。这些机制使AWS能够在公司需要时对数据进行加密和解密。公司与AWS之间未签订数据处理协议。"
